channel.title: Lots of trouble with PI
channel.description: I am trying to start work on a server using PI as a base but whenever I edit files nothing changes. I have tried editing global objects (as mentioned here: https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,644491.0.html ), I have tried adding commands and I have tried changing starter items. I have followed tutorials 100% and where others have success I do not. Once I add my code and compile there has been ZERO change in game. I honestly dont know what I am missing! Please help :(

item.title: Lots of trouble with PI
item.dc:creator: @Kuhgar Kuhgar
item.description:
@Kuhgar wrote:

Here is from another post I made on the same topic:

Hey, Im trying to add global objects to my PI server. So I went into ObjectManager.java and found:
public void loadCustomSpawns(Client client)
So I added my object in under there (in this case a bank booth). I added it as:
client.getPA().checkObjectSpawn(2213, 3093, 3493, 2, 10);
After I saved, compiled and restarted my object was nowhere to be seen. There is also a lack of results when I try to edit the location of preexisting objects.

Hopefully that gives more info.
